    {
      "id": "d12ece27_f607a42f",
      "file_path": "aai-traversal/src/test/java/org/onap/aai/rest/search/GenericQueryProcessorTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 107,
      "message": "This test only deals with the 'if query shorter than dsl query end, return query' bit:\n```java\nString end = \".cap('x').unfold().dedup()\";\nif (query.length() <= end.length()) {\n    return query;\n}\n```\nCan you add another test that tests `String dslQuery = \"some dsl query.cap('x').unfold().dedup()\";`?\nI think the test method name should be adjusted then too, to something like `testAsTreeParameterWithDslQueryShorterThanQueryEnd` and `testAsTreeParameterWithDslQueryLongerThanQueryEnd` maybe",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7849,
        "name": "Fiete Ostkamp",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de",
        "username": "fostkamp"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-24 07:20:23.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a0d0946e_e31a9fe7",
      "file_path": "aai-traversal/src/test/java/org/onap/aai/rest/search/ModelAndNamedQueryRestProviderTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 202,
      "message": "Please don't assert what you are NOT expecting. That doesn't make any sense at all.\nRather assert here that you are expecting a `Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST.getStatusCode()` here and also the specific response body:\n```java\nassertEquals(Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST.getStatusCode(), response.getStatus());\nString expectedResponseEntity = \"\"\"\n        {\"requestError\":{\"serviceException\":{\"messageId\":\"SVC3000\",\"text\":\"Invalid input performing %1 on %2 (msg=%3) (ec=%4)\",\"variables\":[\"POST Search\",\"getModelQueryResponse\",\"Required Field not passed.:Could not determine the top-node nodeType for this request. modelInfo: []\",\"ERR.5.4.6118\"]}}}\"\"\";\nassertEquals(expectedResponseEntity,response.getEntity());\n```",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7849,
        "name": "Fiete Ostkamp",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de",
        "username": "fostkamp"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-24 07:43:25.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "50c21795_22a71495",
      "file_path": "aai-traversal/src/test/java/org/onap/aai/rest/search/ModelAndNamedQueryRestProviderTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 216,
      "message": "Please assert the response entity here.\nAlso your method is called ``...InvalidHeaders`, while what you are testing here is rather that `RuntimeExceptions` are caught and mapped to error responses.\n\nI would suggest that you either rename the test message to something like `testModelQueryRuntimeExceptionsAreCaught`, or if it is specifically about testing that the `xFromAppId` header may not be `null`, then adjust this testcase to `when(httpHeaders.getRequestHeader(\"X-FromAppId\")).thenReturn(null)` and assert the `AAIException` that is caught and mapped to some error response",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7849,
        "name": "Fiete Ostkamp",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de",
        "username": "fostkamp"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-24 08:07:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
